{
  "text": "The long-lasting hyperpolarization, while K+ mediated, is also not a \"spontaneous\" I-IPSP. While Cs+ reduced both potentials, spontaneous hyperpolarizations were reduced more effectively and in considerably shorter periods of time. The reduced access of Cs+ to the synaptic potential may indicate a distant site of generation. These findings corroborate recent work indicating that while NB stimulation completely eliminates spontaneous hyperpolarizations, only sometimes does it reduce the I-IPSP, and then only partly [CITATION_1] .",
